text: Duplicaria hiradoensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae, the auger snails. ==Description== The snail has an auger-shaped shell about 40–55 mm long.Duplicaria hiradoensis — Hardy's Internet Guide to Marine Gastropods on Gastropods.com ==Distribution== ==References== Category:Terebridae Category:Gastropods described in 1921
title: Duplicaria hiradoensis
